claim.claim-text:
A solar power generation system that interconnects with an alternating current power system, the solar power generation system characterized by comprising:
a solar cell;
an inverter that converts a direct current power generated by the solar cell into an alternating current power;
system voltage measurement means for measuring a system voltage of the alternating current power system;
voltage drop detection means for detecting a voltage drop of the alternating current power system, based on the system voltage measured by the system voltage measurement means;
first direct current voltage control means for controlling a direct current voltage of the inverter to enhance a power generation efficiency of the solar cell, when the voltage drop is not detected by the voltage drop detection means; and
second direct current voltage control means for controlling the direct current voltage of the inverter to suppress a current output from the inverter, when the voltage drop is detected by the voltage drop detection means.

A control apparatus for an inverter that controls the inverter to be applied to a solar power generation system interconnecting with an alternating current power system and including a solar cell, the control apparatus characterized by comprising:
system voltage measurement means for measuring a system voltage of the alternating current power system;
voltage drop detection means for detecting a voltage drop of the alternating current power system, based on the system voltage measured by the system voltage measurement means;
first direct current voltage control means for controlling a direct current voltage of the inverter to enhance a power generation efficiency of the solar cell, when the voltage drop is not detected by the voltage drop detection means; and
second direct current voltage control means for controlling the direct current voltage of the inverter to suppress a current output from the inverter, when the voltage drop is detected by the voltage drop detection means.

A control method for an inverter that controls the inverter to be applied to a solar power generation system interconnecting with an alternating current power system and including a solar cell, the control method characterized by comprising:
measuring a system voltage of the alternating current power system;
detecting a voltage drop of the alternating current power system, based on the measured system voltage;
controlling a direct current voltage of the inverter to enhance a power generation efficiency of the solar cell, when the voltage drop of the alternating current power system is not detected; and
controlling the direct current voltage of the inverter to suppress a current output from the inverter, when the voltage drop of the alternating current power system is detected.
